    <p class="eyebrow">World</p>
    <h1>The Warm Remembering</h1>
    <p class="lede">The Warm Remembering is part of how memory, care, and continuity are understood in Vaelinya.</p>
    <p>It carries the idea that remembering can be lived, shared, and held through people, language, place, and relationship rather than only records or isolated facts.</p>
    <p>Memory in Vaelinya can belong to households, roads, names, repeated acts, songs, witness, and shared attention. A remembered thing may stay alive because people continue to carry it together.</p>
    <p>The Warm Remembering gives emotional and civic depth to the world. It asks what should be held, what should be passed onward, and how care can survive through change.</p>
